OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA mainly dry with variable
OL,6,Famounts of cloud and some bright or
OL,7,Fsunny spells. A few showers may break
OL,8,Fout, these mainly across the south and
OL,9,Feast.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FAny showers slowly dying out
OL,12,Fthis evening. Then the rest of the
OL,13,Fnight will be dry with variable
OL,14,Famounts of cloud. A cold night with
OL,15,Fpatchy frost.
OL,16,
OL,17,CSunday:FAfter a cold start the morning
OL,18,Fwill be dry and bright. Staying dry in
OL,19,Fthe afternoon but clouding over.
OL,20,FPatchy rain spreading south in the
OL,21,Fevening.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
